      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine and a 6-speed manual gearbox. This unit benefits from proactive maintenance, including a documented VANOS rebuild and structural subframe reinforcement to ensure chassis rigidity. The factory limited-slip differential and individual throttle bodies remain in excellent working order, providing the sharp throttle response and mid-corner poise these cars are known for. Recent preventative maintenance includes a valve clearance adjustment and cooling system refresh. While the exterior shows minor patina, the drivetrain is dialed in for performance, offering a pure, analog connection to the road.",
